# Authentication & Authorization: Clerk Route Protection

All pages and layouts that require authentication **must** verify the user with Clerk and redirect unauthenticated visitors immediately.

## Protected Pages

Use Clerk's `auth()` in Server Components or layouts to guard routes.

```typescript
// in page.tsx or layout.tsx
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";

export default async function ProtectedPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) redirect("/sign-in");

  // safe to render authenticated content
}
```

## Protected Server Actions

Every Server Action that reads or mutates data must also call `auth()` and reject unauthenticated requests.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — auth check at the top of every action
"use server";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

export async function myAction(input: MyInput) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
  // ...
}

// ❌ BAD — no auth check; any caller can invoke the action
export async function myAction(input: MyInput) {
  await db.insert(decks).values({ ... });
}
```

## Rules

- Call `auth()` at the top of every protected page, layout, and Server Action.
- Redirect with `redirect("/sign-in")` in pages/layouts; throw `new Error("Unauthorized")` in actions.
- Never trust a user-supplied `userId` — always read it from `auth()`.
- Scope all database queries to the authenticated `userId` (see `clerk-auth-data-isolation` rule).
